This paper deals with predicting delayed outcomes in recommender systems using neural network architectures. The problem is formulated as an adversarial, delayed online learning problem, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of proxies to minimize regret, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with predicting human behavior, which is relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
